FBIS3-49574 "dreeu008_i_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Muslims Continue Attack on Vitez, Novi Travnik LD1101190994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1816 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101190994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Report by Zdenko Vranjes] [Excerpt] The Muslim army today continued to attack the Vitez and Novi Travnik areas and a general alert was also sounded in Kiseljak. Heavy street fighting is still under way in the area of Buhine Kuce, on the eastern approaches to Vitez. The Muslim units, reinforced with new forces from Zenica, are still trying to regain the positions they lost yesterday and get access to the Vitez-Busovaca road. The Muslim army continues to pound the center of Vitez, using mortars and heavy guns. Novi Travnik has also been shelled throughout the day, as have the surrounding areas held by the Croatian Defense Council [HVO]heavily pounded from the Muslim howitzers and mortars are the town centernd the area of Rastovci. It has been reported from Novi Travnik that the HVO repelled a heavy infantry attack on Relej, a hill near the town. The Muslim forces suffered a major defeat and were forced to withdraw, with heavy losses. [passage omitted]
